<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,1473,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,472,1473,1499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Distribution.</emphasis>
The discovery of 
<taxonomicName box="[697,872,1473,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaliscoensis">
<emphasis box="[697,872,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. jaliscoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extends the distribution of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[264,368,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[264,368,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ceraspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<geoCoordinate box="[442,553,1513,1539]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" precision="925" value="18.75">
<number box="[442,470,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="18.0">18</number>
º 
<number box="[489,521,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="45.0">45</number>
' N
</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate box="[592,702,1513,1539]" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" precision="925" value="20.45">
<number box="[592,621,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="20.0">20</number>
º 
<number box="[639,671,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="27.0">27</number>
' N
</geoCoordinate>
(
<figureCitation box="[720,834,1513,1539]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5" captionStart-1="FIGURE 6" captionStart-2="FIGURE 7" captionStartId-0="4.[264,368,1050,1074]" captionStartId-1="4.[264,368,1841,1865]" captionStartId-2="5.[264,368,923,947]" captionTargetBox-0="[408,1192,460,1050]" captionTargetBox-1="[428,1192,1222,1786]" captionTargetBox-2="[411,1174,328,892]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[407,1192,448,1050]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[414,1207,1207,1823]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[400,1187,315,916]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURE 5. Distribution of the Mexican species of Ceraspis. C. jaliscoensis (triangles), C. oaxacaensis (square) and, C. velutina (circles)." captionText-1="FIGURE 6. Distribution of the Mexican species of Ceraspis. C. mexicana (circles) and, C. centralis (squares)." captionText-2="FIGURE 7. Distribution of Ceraspis pilatei (circles; empty diamonds, country record without specific data)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/158247/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/158248/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/158249/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[787,834,1513,1539]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). The new species is found at the highest altitude of any species of this genus (
<quantity box="[700,803,1553,1579]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.433" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="m" value="1433.0">1,433 m</quantity>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[855,948,1553,1579]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">México</collectingCountry>
, others species are found below 
<quantity box="[264,360,1593,1619]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="m" value="1000.0">1,000 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Delgado" box="[376,613,1593,1619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refString="Delgado, L., Deloya, C. &amp; Moron, M. A. (1987) Descripcion del macho de Ceraspis velutina (Bates) y nuevos registros de C. centralis (Sharp) para Mexico (Coleoptera: Melolonthidae; Macrodactylini). Folia Entomologica Mexicana, 71, 47 - 54." type="journal article" year="1987">
Delgado et al. 
<number box="[550,613,1593,1619]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[1011,1182,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaliscoensis">
<emphasis box="[1011,1182,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. jaliscoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
extends the range more than 
<quantity box="[463,553,1633,1659]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="km" value="670.0">670 km</quantity>
west in 
<collectingCountry box="[652,741,1633,1659]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">México</collectingCountry>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[758,895,1633,1659]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" precision="925" value="-104.75">
<number box="[758,803,1633,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="104.0">104</number>
º 
<number box="[820,852,1633,1659]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="45.0">45</number>
' W
</geoCoordinate>
). Three species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1116,1220,1633,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1220,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ceraspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are now endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[403,497,1673,1699]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">México</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[509,689,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oaxacaensis">
<emphasis box="[509,689,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. oaxacaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Oaxaca), 
<taxonomicName box="[820,951,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis box="[820,951,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Guerrero), and 
<taxonomicName box="[1150,1323,1673,1698]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaliscoensis">
<emphasis box="[1150,1323,1673,1698]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">C. jaliscoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jalisco) (
<figureCitation box="[382,456,1713,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1050,1074]" captionTargetBox="[408,1192,460,1050]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[407,1192,448,1050]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution of the Mexican species of Ceraspis. C. jaliscoensis (triangles), C. oaxacaensis (square) and, C. velutina (circles)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158247/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[439,456,1713,1739]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). The remaining non­endemic species occur in southern Mexican states south to 
<collectingCountry box="[365,458,1753,1779]" name="Panama" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Panamá</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[474,588,1753,1779]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 6" captionStart-1="FIGURE 7" captionStartId-0="4.[264,368,1841,1865]" captionStartId-1="5.[264,368,923,947]" captionTargetBox-0="[428,1192,1222,1786]" captionTargetBox-1="[411,1174,328,892]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[414,1207,1207,1823]" captionTargetId-1="figure@5.[400,1187,315,916]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="FIGURE 6. Distribution of the Mexican species of Ceraspis. C. mexicana (circles) and, C. centralis (squares)." captionText-1="FIGURE 7. Distribution of Ceraspis pilatei (circles; empty diamonds, country record without specific data)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/158248/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/158249/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Figs. 
<number box="[540,588,1753,1779]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1324,1473,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,449,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Bionomics.</emphasis>
The adults were collected on grass (
<specimenCount box="[881,1016,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="generic">
<number box="[881,894,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
specimen
</specimenCount>
), under moss (
<number box="[1187,1203,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
) and, in a carrion trap baited with squid (
<number box="[630,643,1833,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
). The carrion­baited trap was probably an accidental capture, since the adults of this genus feed on flowers (
<bibRefCitation author="Capistran" box="[867,1196,1873,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="6" refString="Capistran, F. &amp; Aquino, O. (1992) Observaciones sobre la biologia de Ceraspis pilatei Harold (Coleoptera: Melolonthidae), en el area de Catemaco, Veracruz, Mexico. Folia Entomologica Mexicana, 85, 119 - 122." type="journal article" year="1992">
Capistrán and Aquino 
<number box="[1133,1196,1873,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1322,283,350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,452,283,309]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName box="[719,856,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Ceraspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaliscoensis">
<emphasis box="[719,856,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">jaliscoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, refers to Jalisco, the state where was collected this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
